---
import MainLayout from '../../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
import CTA from '../../components/CTA.astro';

const pageDescription = "Protect your vision with expert medical retina care. We specialize in advanced diagnostics and evidence-based treatments for diabetic retinopathy and macular degeneration in KK Nagar.";
---

<MainLayout title="Medical Retina Care in Chennai" description={pageDescription}>  <!-- Service Header -->
  <section class="bg-blue-900 text-white py-20 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center gap-12">
      <div class="md:w-1/2">
        <span class="text-blue-300 font-bold tracking-wider uppercase text-sm mb-4 block">Diagnostic Intelligence</span>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold mb-6 leading-tight">Medical Retina Care</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-blue-100 mb-8 leading-relaxed">
          Expert diagnosis and management of Diabetic Retinopathy, Macular Degeneration, and complex retinal disorders.
        </p>
        <a href="#book" class="bg-white text-blue-900 font-bold px-8 py-3 rounded-md shadow-lg hover:bg-blue-50 transition inline-block">Schedule a Retina Scan</a>
      </div>
      <div class="md:w-1/2 w-full">
        <img src="/images/retina.jpg" alt="Digital retinal imaging and diagnostic scan" class="rounded-2xl shadow-2xl border-4 border-white/10 w-full object-cover aspect-video" onerror="this.src='https://placehold.co/800x500/1e3a8a/ffffff?text=Retinal+Diagnostics'"/>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Content Section -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <div class="prose prose-lg prose-blue max-w-none text-slate-700">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-blue-900 mb-6">Protecting the Back of Your Eye</h2>
      <p class="mb-6">
        The retina is the light-sensitive layer of tissue at the back of the inner eye, acting much like the film in a camera. Damage to the retina can cause permanent, irreversible vision loss if not caught early. We specialize in the early detection and evidence-based management of retinal diseases.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-blue-900 mt-12 mb-6">Diabetic Retinopathy</h2>
      <p class="mb-6">
        Diabetes can cause damage to the blood vessels in the retina. In its early stages, diabetic retinopathy often has no symptoms. However, as the disease progresses, it can lead to severe vision loss. <strong>If you have diabetes, an annual dilated eye exam is absolutely critical.</strong>
      </p>
      
      <div class="bg-blue-50 p-8 rounded-xl border border-blue-100 my-10">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-blue-900 mb-4">Advanced Diagnostic Technology</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 font-medium">
          <li><strong>Optical Coherence Tomography (OCT):</strong> A non-invasive imaging test that uses light waves to take cross-section pictures of your retina, allowing us to see each of the retina's distinctive layers.</li>
          <li><strong>Fundus Photography:</strong> High-resolution digital imaging to monitor disease progression over time.</li>
          <li><strong>Targeted Treatments:</strong> Including precise retinal lasers and anti-VEGF intraocular injections to halt disease progression.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-blue-900 mt-12 mb-6">Age-Related Macular Degeneration (AMD)</h2>
      <p class="mb-6">
        AMD affects the macula, the central part of the retina responsible for sharp, straight-ahead vision. We offer comprehensive management plans for both "Dry" and "Wet" macular degeneration to help preserve your central vision and maintain your quality of life.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTA 
    title="Book Your Retina Evaluation"
    address="39/2, R K Shanmugam Salai, K K Nagar, Chennai – 600078"
    phone="+91 63813 02828"
  />
</MainLayout>
